reply_text:
@Frost_the_polarian_fox the 80 Asterix and the Big Fight version is one of the most beloved in France, I'm French and the sense of threat and sadness was on point, when the romans are inside the village is one of the most emotional Asterix & Obelix  sequence you'll ever have, there is a lot of thought in the 89 version, this one is just an inside joke made by Alain Chabat (a great dude tho) that only french can understand sometimes.
Exemple the strawberry and lobster (in french it's Fraise and Homard ) sequence is a "joke", it's a reference to Omar and Fred, a comical french duo.
there's a lot of cronyism in this series, with Chabat's friends getting involved, sometimes unnecessarily (at least in the french version)... but it's still a high-quality animated film.
